metadata.name: we have trees in afterlife #43
metadata.description:
When you are in a dream, it is very difficult to know that you are dreaming.
Most of the time what is in the dream becomes reality itself, and I believe it is the same in the afterlife, or maybe not... Who knows?
This project portrays my imagination about the fantastic worlds we visit while we are dreaming, and we only know it wasn't real after waking up.
What is real?
I tried to simulate the confusion of a dream. The branches and spirals represent each memory that when put together they form this, while in the background is overshadowing and makes us remember few things when we wake up.

Each piece has its unique properties like pallets, growth patterns, colors, shades...

This is a project made in p5.js

metadata.name: Pigeon Sat on a Brain Reflecting Existence #44
metadata.description:
Why am I here? the pigeon asked.
And what must I do?
And what are you doing?
My work is done.
And so is yours.
We are but birds,
A moment’s thought can teach us
That the sun moves and that the stars
Are worlds like ours; that the rain
Has its time of falling.
What a strange thought!
We are but birds,
Nothing more,
All is one.

metadata.name: Mixed Signals #54
metadata.description:
Mixed Signals is a series of 128 generative animated loops. Each animation is constructed with a grid of curves that creates illusions of waveforms marching across the screen or shapes bubbling in and out of existence. Some rare mints are possible, since features are available in the following categories:

extremely low, very low, low, medium, high, very high, extremely high

where medium is the most common, low and high are rarer, very low and very high are even rarer, etc.

Interactions:
Ctrl+S / Cmd+S: Save a 2048 x 2048 screen capture
Ctrl+Shift+S / Cmd+Shift+S (Press, don't hold): Export image sequence of 3 second loop 
Space bar: Pause/Unpause the animation

Original artwork by Stephen Jue · Made with canvas-sketch · 2022

metadata.name: Tally! #6808
metadata.description:
Tally! Is a year long, free, open edition to celebrate fxhash v2. Data from the minting of Tally! will be used to create other new artworks.

This artwork is simply about counting up from one to wherever we end up, with a litle bit of Fizz Buzz thrown in. Mints that have a prime numbers* as factors will have slight variations. Sometimes those variations will combine, sometimes you have to get to really high numbers for multiple prime numbers to combine.

Where the finally Tally! ends up who knows? But there's going to be a lot of tallying along the way, and it'll give you something to do while waiting between other mints.

INSTRUCTIONS ::

'?forceWidth=xxxx' on the end of the URL to change the width of the image
's' = save image

metadata.name: Edge #155
metadata.description: This collaboration was destined to happen. The joint effort of two landscape enthusiasts, each with a distinct approach to creation and style, resulted in something new for both. 'Edge' is a project showcasing subtle lines that connect in the subconscious something not opposing but slightly different. It's the edge that separates the dusty country road you're driving on from the beautiful, colorful landscape outside the car window. It's the edge that almost imperceptibly divides day and night during sunrises and sunsets. It's the edge where AI and generative art have converged...
